# ===================================================================
# REST Client for Zed - Example Requests
# ===================================================================
#
# HOW TO SEND REQUESTS:
#   1. Press: Cmd+Shift+P (Mac) or Ctrl+Shift+P (Windows/Linux)
#   2. Type: "spawn" or "task"
#   3. Select: "task: spawn"
#   4. Select: "Send Request"
#   5. View response in the terminal panel!
#
# OR use the command line:
#   cargo run --release --features cli --bin http-execute test.http
#
# See HOW_TO_SEND.md for keyboard shortcut setup
# ===================================================================

### Get a random user
GET https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users/1

###
### Get all posts
GET https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts

### Create a new post
POST https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "My New Post",
  "body": "This is the content of my post",
  "userId": 1
}

### Update a post
PUT https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 1,
  "title": "Updated Title",
  "body": "Updated content",
  "userId": 1
}

### Delete a post
DELETE https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts/1

### Test with headers
GET https://httpbin.org/headers
User-Agent: REST Client Test
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer fake-token-for-testing

### Test with query parameters
GET https://httpbin.org/get?name=test&value=123

### Test POST with form data
POST https://httpbin.org/post
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

name=John&email=john@example.com&message=Hello

### Variables example (parsed but not executed yet)
@baseUrl = https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com
@userId = 5

GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}

###
### Get user's posts
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts?userId={{userId}}
